		"priority": 18,
		"req_level": 7,
		"once_ever": true,
		"branch_at": 4,
		"script": [
			{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "Larder's honest in a way people hate. Grain's short enough that 'seconds' is a lie we can cook—or a truth we can swallow."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "What do you recommend?"},
			{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "I can stretch the kettle—salt, time, noise—so bellies feel fuller than the tally. Or I can say the tally plain at the line and let worry sit where it belongs."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Morale matters."},
			{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "So does tomorrow's march. Pick: feed hope with a story tonight… or keep mouths honest and trust them not to go feral when the pot tells the truth?"},
		],
		"choices": [
			{
				"text": "Tell the truth plain. I'll back you.",
				"result": "success",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "No soft lie in the larder. We'll ration like adults and I'll say why."},
					{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "Good. Hunger's sharper than surprise. Surprise turns camps cruel."},
					{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "I'll keep the portions even and the words small. A camp stays human when nobody's stealing shame along with bread."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "You sound like you've seen the other way."},
					{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "I've seen what happens when the pot pretends and the body remembers. Honesty isn't cruelty—it's the kind of care that doesn't waste your next week."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 2},
			},
			{
				"text": "Stretch the kettle. Buy us calm tonight.",
				"result": "fail",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Thin the broth, add time—whatever keeps the line steady. I'll fix supply tomorrow."},
					{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "I'll do it. But hear me: this is a loan, not a miracle."},
					{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "When the debt comes due, pay it in rations—not speeches. Speeches don't fill hands."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "You'll get the grain."},
					{"speaker": "Branik", "text": "Then we're square enough. I shield when I can. I won't shield you from your own books forever."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 1},
			},
		],
		"effects_on_complete": {"advance_personal_arc_stage": 1, "set_arc_flag": "dc_camp_avatar_branik_2"},
	},
	{
		"id": "dc_camp_avatar_sorrel_1",
		"primary_unit": "Sorrel",
		"participants": ["Sorrel", "Commander"],
		"conversation_type": "support",
		"priority": 18,
		"req_level": 4,
		"once_ever": true,
		"branch_at": 4,
		"script": [
			{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "You asked for my notes on supply routes. I gave you probabilities. You looked disappointed."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "I wanted something firmer."},
			{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Firm is a luxury. What you have is evidence and educated fear."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Fear isn't a plan."},
			{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "No—but ignoring fear is how plans become anecdotes. Tell me, Commander: do you want the map that comforts you, or the one that keeps you alive?"},
		],
		"choices": [
			{
				"text": "The one that keeps us alive.",
				"result": "success",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Give me the ugly numbers. I'll carry them."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Better. Ugly numbers age well."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "I'll revise the margins tonight. If I'm harsh, it's because mercy on paper gets people killed on roads."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Then be harsh."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "As you like. Try not to flinch when the ink agrees with me."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 2},
			},
			{
				"text": "We need morale as much as math.",
				"result": "fail",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "If everything sounds like defeat, the camp hears it."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "If everything sounds like victory, the camp stops looking."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "We can speak two truths: one for the hearth, one for the ledger. Do not ask me to lie on the ledger."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "I wasn't asking for lies."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Good. Then we understand each other—barely, but it's a start."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 1},
			},
		],
		"effects_on_complete": {"advance_personal_arc_stage": 1, "set_arc_flag": "dc_camp_avatar_sorrel_1"},
	},
	{
		"id": "dc_camp_avatar_sorrel_2",
		"primary_unit": "Sorrel",
		"participants": ["Sorrel", "Commander"],
		"conversation_type": "support",
		"priority": 17,
		"req_level": 8,
		"once_ever": true,
		"branch_at": 4,
		"script": [
			{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "I turned a page and found someone else's anger in the margin—a supply fork the College marked 'sealed' while carts still rolled."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Is it usable?"},
			{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Usable is simple. Contagious is the problem. Raw ink makes captains hunt for traitors; trimmed ink makes them confident too soon."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "What are you offering?"},
			{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "The excerpt exactly as written—teeth, blame, uncertainty intact—or my reading: shaped for movement, with my judgment smeared all over the frame. Rigor that cuts… or interpretation that carries?"},
		],
		"choices": [
			{
				"text": "Raw. I want the source, not your varnish.",
				"result": "success",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Bring the fragment. I'll decide how it lives in orders—without you laundering it first."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Good. If we're administrating ignorance, let it be visible administration."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "You'll get copies with stains. If someone flinches, that's data too."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "I'll take the flinch."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Then we're aligned—barely. Curiosity isn't kindness. It's responsibility with teeth. Don't ask me to file them down until you've earned the right."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 2},
			},
			{
				"text": "Shape it. I need movement without a mutiny over ink.",
				"result": "fail",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Give me what we can act on. Hold the commentary that turns officers into prosecutors."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Hmph. Practical heresy. I'll do it—and I'll keep a clean copy for myself where the blood stays visible."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "If the shaped version lies by omission, that's on both of us. I won't pretend otherwise."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Noted."},
					{"speaker": "Sorrel", "text": "Good. Knowledge isn't innocent in camps. It's just sometimes less murderous when it's translated—unfortunately."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 1},
			},
		],
		"effects_on_complete": {"advance_personal_arc_stage": 1, "set_arc_flag": "dc_camp_avatar_sorrel_2"},
	},
	{
		"id": "dc_camp_avatar_tamsin_1",
		"primary_unit": "Tamsin Reed",
		"participants": ["Tamsin Reed", "Commander"],
		"conversation_type": "support",
		"priority": 19,
		"req_level": 2,
		"once_ever": true,
		"branch_at": 4,
		"script": [
			{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Pot's thin tonight. Not dangerously—just honest. Someone always asks for seconds like it's a verdict on my character."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Do you want me to say something to the line?"},
			{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "I want you to decide what kind of hungry we are. Belly-hungry, or fear-hungry."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Both show up the same in a queue."},
			{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "True. So pick your doctrine, Commander: feed everyone until the pot lies, or ration like adults and keep tomorrow from being a rumor?"},
		],
		"choices": [
			{
				"text": "Ration. Explain it plain.",
				"result": "success",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "I'll tell them we're stretching so we don't break. No shame in that."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Good. Shame makes people steal spoons and pride."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "I'll make the next kettle taste like someone cared—even if the portion doesn't."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "You already do."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Flattery won't get you extra bread. It might get you a thicker broth. We'll see."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 2},
			},
			{
				"text": "Fill bowls tonight. We'll solve tomorrow tomorrow.",
				"result": "fail",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Morale can't eat a speech."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Morale can't eat air either, but go on."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "I'll stretch it. You'll owe the larder an apology later—and you'll pay it in better supply, I hope."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "I'll pay it."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "See that you do. I'm too tired to be angry and cook at the same time."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 1},
			},
		],
		"effects_on_complete": {"advance_personal_arc_stage": 1, "set_arc_flag": "dc_camp_avatar_tamsin_1"},
	},
	{
		"id": "dc_camp_avatar_tamsin_2",
		"primary_unit": "Tamsin Reed",
		"participants": ["Tamsin Reed", "Commander"],
		"conversation_type": "support",
		"priority": 18,
		"req_level": 6,
		"once_ever": true,
		"branch_at": 4,
		"script": [
			{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Four cots, six bodies' worth of hurt, two hands, one stove that thinks it's funny. The fever in the corner is winning faster than my jokes are."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "What do you need?"},
			{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Permission to be cruel in the right direction—or kindness that lies well. That spike will crash without concentrated hours. The others can limp on bark and spite."},
			{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "You're asking who gets the truth."},
			{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Triage isn't polite. Do I camp on the worst case where everyone can see me being heroic… or spread care thin so four people stay equally angry and equally alive?"},
		],
		"choices": [
			{
				"text": "The worst case. Steal the hours. I'll explain the line.",
				"result": "success",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Concentrate on who'll die without you. I'll handle the muttering."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Good. Heroics are cheaper when they're honest about who pays."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "I'll sweat the ugly work. If someone calls me selfish, tell them selfish kept breath in the room."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Rest after."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Rest is a fantasy I visit after the list stops screaming. Humor me with water and no speeches about grace—I get enough of that from fevers."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 2},
			},
			{
				"text": "Spread it. No one gets left to feel abandoned.",
				"result": "fail",
				"response": [
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Fair shares. We'll move volunteers if we have to."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Fair shares are a morale religion. Biology isn't democratic."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "I'll rotate anyway—because you asked—and I'll document who got what, when the shouting starts."},
					{"speaker": "Commander", "text": "Fair."},
					{"speaker": "Tamsin Reed", "text": "Fair's a thin blanket. I'll still use it—just don't ask me to pretend it's warm."},
				],
				"effects": {"add_avatar_relationship": 1},
			},
		],
		"effects_on_complete": {"advance_personal_arc_stage": 1, "set_arc_flag": "dc_camp_avatar_tamsin_2"},
	},
	{
		"id": "dc_camp_avatar_celia_1",
		"primary_unit": "Celia",
		"participants": ["Celia", "Commander"],
